import cv2   
import numpy as np
cv2.namedWindow('hsv')
#capturing video through webcam
cap=cv2.VideoCapture(0)
def callback(x):
        pass

def pick_color(event,x,y,flags,param):
    if event == cv2.EVENT_LBUTTONDOWN:
        pixel = hsv[y,x]

        #you might want to adjust the ranges(+-10, etc):
        upper =  np.array([pixel[0] + 10, pixel[1] + 10, pixel[2] + 40])
        lower =  np.array([pixel[0] - 10, pixel[1] - 10, pixel[2] - 40])
        print(pixel, lower, upper)
        ilowh=pixel[0] - 10;
        ihighh = pixel[0] + 10;
        ilows = pixel[1] - 10;
        ihighs = pixel[1] + 10;
        ilowv = pixel[2] - 40;
        ihighv = pixel[2] + 40;
        if(mode==0):
        
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lowh','image',pixel[0] - 10)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highh','image',pixel[0] + 10)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lows','image',pixel[1] - 20)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highs','image',pixel[1] + 20)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lowv','image',pixel[2] - 50)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highv','image',pixel[2] + 50)
        elif(mode==1):
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lowh','image',pixel[0] - 10)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highh','image',pixel[0] + 10)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lows','image',pixel[1] - 20)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highs','image',pixel[1] + 20)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lowv','image',pixel[2] - 50)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highv','image',pixel[2] + 50)
        elif(mode==2):
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lowh','image',pixel[0] - 10)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highh','image',pixel[0] + 10)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lows','image',pixel[1] - 20)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highs','image',pixel[1] + 20)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('lowv','image',pixel[2] - 50)
                cv2.setTrackbarPos('highv','image',pixel[2] + 50)
                
        #image_mask = cv2.inRange(image_hsv,lower,upper)
        #cv2.imshow("mask",image_mask)
ilowh=136;
ihighh = 186;
ilows = 87;
ihighs = 255;
ilowv = 0;
ihighv = 255;
mode=0;
ilowh1=0;
ihighh1 = 179;
ilows1 = 0;
ihighs1 = 255;
ilowv1 = 0;
ihighv1 = 255;

ilowh2=22;
ihighh2 = 60;
ilows2 = 60;
ihighs2 = 255;
ilowv2 = 200;
ihighv2 = 255;

cv2.namedWindow('image')
cv2.namedWindow('Color Tracking')
cv2.createTrackbar('mode','image',mode,2,callback);

cv2.createTrackbar('lowh','image',ilowh,179,callback);
cv2.createTrackbar('highh','image',ihighh,179,callback);
cv2.createTrackbar('lows','image',ilows,255,callback)
cv2.createTrackbar('highs','image',ihighs,255,callback)
cv2.createTrackbar('lowv','image',ilowv,255,callback)
cv2.createTrackbar('highv','image',ihighv,255,callback)
cv2.setMouseCallback('Color Tracking', pick_color)
while(1):
        _, img = cap.read()
        
        mode=cv2.getTrackbarPos('mode', 'image') 
        hsv=cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)
        if(mode==0):
        
                ilowh=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lowh', 'image')
                ihighh=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highh', 'image')
                ilows=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lows', 'image')
                ihighs=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highs', 'image')
                ilowv=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lowv', 'image')
                ihighv=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highv', 'image')
        elif(mode==1):
                
                ilowh1=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lowh', 'image')
                ihighh1=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highh', 'image')
                ilows1=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lows', 'image')
                ihighs1=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highs', 'image')
                ilowv1=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lowv', 'image')
                ihighv1=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highv', 'image')
        elif(mode==2):
                        
                ilowh2=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lowh', 'image')
                ihighh2=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highh', 'image')
                ilows2=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lows', 'image')
                ihighs2=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highs', 'image')
                ilowv2=cv2.getTrackbarPos('lowv', 'image')
                ihighv2=cv2.getTrackbarPos('highv', 'image')
        #definig the range of red color
        red_lower=np.array([ilowh,ilows,ilowv],np.uint8)
        red_upper=np.array([ihighh,ihighs,ihighv],np.uint8)

        #defining the Range of Blue color
        blue_lower=np.array([ilowh1,ilows1,ilowv1],np.uint8)
        blue_upper=np.array([ihighh1,ihighs1,ihighv1],np.uint8)
        
        #defining the Range of yellow color
        yellow_lower=np.array([ilowh2,ilows2,ilowv2],np.uint8)
        yellow_upper=np.array([ihighh2,ihighs2,ihighv2],np.uint8)

        

        #finding the range of red,blue and yellow color in the image
        red=cv2.inRange(hsv, red_lower, red_upper)
        blue=cv2.inRange(hsv,blue_lower,blue_upper)
        yellow=cv2.inRange(hsv,yellow_lower,yellow_upper)
        
        #Morphological transformation, Dilation         
        kernal = np.ones((5 ,5), "uint8")
        red=cv2.dilate(red, kernal)
        res=cv2.bitwise_and(img, img, mask = red)

        blue=cv2.dilate(blue,kernal)
        res1=cv2.bitwise_and(img, img, mask = blue)
        xupper=450
        xlower=250
        yupper=400
        ylower=100
        yellow=cv2.dilate(yellow,kernal)
        res2=cv2.bitwise_and(img, img, mask = yellow)    
        center = (xlower,ylower)
        cv2.circle(img,center,5,(255,255,255),5)
        center1 = (xupper,yupper)
        cv2.circle(img,center1,5,(255,255,255),5)
        #Tracking the Red Color
        (_,contours,hierarchy)=cv2.findContours(red,cv2.RETR_TREE,cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)
        
        for pic, contour in enumerate(contours):
                area = cv2.contourArea(contour)
                if(area>200 and area<30000):
                        cnt = contours[0]
                        x,y,w,h = cv2.boundingRect(contour)
                        cx=(x+w)-w/2
                        cy=(y+h)-h/2
                        if(cx>xlower and cx<xupper and cy>ylower and cy<yupper):
                                center = (int(cx),int(cy))
                                cv2.circle(img,center,5,(255,255,255),5)
                                img = cv2.rectangle(img,(x,y),(x+w,y+h),(0,0,255),2)
                                cv2.putText(img,"RED color",(x,y),cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.7, (0,0,255))
                        
        #Tracking the Blue Color
        (_,contours,hierarchy)=cv2.findContours(blue,cv2.RETR_TREE,cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)
        for pic, contour in enumerate(contours):
                area = cv2.contourArea(contour)
                if(area>22000):
                        x,y,w,h = cv2.boundingRect(contour)
                        cx=(x+w)-w/2
                        cy=(y+h)-h/2
                        if(cx>xlower and cx<xupper and cy>ylower and cy<yupper):
                                center = (int(cx),int(cy))
                                cv2.circle(img,center,5,(255,255,255),5)
                                img = cv2.rectangle(img,(x,y),(x+w,y+h),(255,0,0),2)
                                cv2.putText(img,"Blue color",(x,y),cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.7, (255,0,0))

        #Tracking the yellow Color
        (_,contours,hierarchy)=cv2.findContours(yellow,cv2.RETR_TREE,cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)
        for pic, contour in enumerate(contours):
                area = cv2.contourArea(contour)
                if(area>22000):
                        x,y,w,h = cv2.boundingRect(contour)     
                        img = cv2.rectangle(img,(x,y),(x+w,y+h),(0,255,0),2)
                        cx=(x+w)-w/2
                        cy=(y+h)-h/2
                        if(cx>xlower and cx<xupper and cy>ylower and cy<yupper):
                                center = (int(cx),int(cy))
                                cv2.circle(img,center,5,(255,255,0),5)
                                cv2.putText(img,"yellow  color",(x,y),cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 1.0, (0,255,0))  
            
           
        #cv2.imshow("Redcolour",red)
        cv2.imshow("Color Tracking",img)
        cv2.imshow("red",res)
        cv2.imshow("blue",res1)
        cv2.imshow("yellow",res2)
        cv2.imshow("hsv",hsv)    
        #cv2.imshow("red",res)  
        if cv2.waitKey(10) & 0xFF == ord('q'):
                cap.release()
                cv2.destroyAllWindows()
                break
